The paper focuses on the use of knowledge possessed by designers and their actual work situation, which suggests a strong emphasis on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The study also involves empirical observations and data collection, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper discusses global and local strategies in design, which could relate to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
